solar masses.
A million to ten million.

00:55:46.860 --> 00:55:50.780
And we can infer that from the motions of
the stars in the galaxy.

00:55:50.780 --> 00:55:56.141
It turns out that these are some of the dark
matter richest objects that are known in the

00:55:56.141 --> 00:56:02.810
universe.
And so we're -- we're really probing the numbers

00:56:02.810 --> 00:56:07.260
of these, their dark
matter content, how the dark matter is distributed

00:56:07.260 --> 00:56:11.560
within them.
Cause they give us the best information about

00:56:11.560 --> 00:56:16.620
the clustering length of the dark matter.
Different forms of dark matter will cluster

00:56:16.620 --> 00:56:20.990
on different scales.
And by, by having dark matter cluster on a

00:56:20.990 --> 00:56:28.870
rather small physical scale, it rules out
a number of different types of dark matter,

00:56:28.870 --> 00:56:32.200
different types of particles that could make
up the dark matter.

00:56:32.200 --> 00:56:36.810
And we're very much involved in exploring,
with these dwarf

00:56:36.810 --> 00:56:43.850
