The hierarchal structure formation theory

00:56:43.850 --> 00:56:48.330
that says there were --
there was a lot of aggregation of dark matter

00:56:48.330 --> 00:56:52.100
into these dwarf galaxy-sized chunks early
in the universe.

00:56:52.100 --> 00:56:59.350
And that big galaxies formed by aggregating
or merging, you know, these small dark matter

00:56:59.350 --> 00:57:03.130
clumps.
So we're testing that theory in great depth

00:57:03.130 --> 00:57:08.380
around the Milky Way and around M-31.

